719292f-a.title: Manhattan: Delancey Street - Willett Street
719292f-a.text:
Delancey Street, north side, at ''illett Street, showing both
N.E. and N.V. corners at this point. To the east of the former
is a 2 and a half story house (No.234) sandwiched between
tenements. These are No'g 232 and 236; the 7 story structure
being the first rentioned. At the oppo-aite corner and only
partially seen is a 6 story building bearing No's 222-226
Delancey Street and No. 45 'illett Street. The photographer
is standing under the Ailliamsburg Bridge approach and is view-
ing north eastward from Sheriff Street.
April 14, 1928
P.L.Sperr

724773f.title: Manhattan: Willett Street - Delancey Street
724773f.text:
Willett Street, at, adjoining and south of the S. E. cor-
ner of Delancey Street, showing structures that are to be
demolished as being in the way of the Williamsburg Bridge.
Delancey Street is at the left and the view is eastward.
Abouy 1901
Ewing Galloway
